Francine, hi!
It's me -- Stan!

13:30.411 --> 13:31.810
I was
at your wedding!

13:31.812 --> 13:33.878
She's looking.
Pretend I said something funny.

13:33.880 --> 13:35.748
We're the guys
who are always laughing.

13:35.750 --> 13:39.884
[ Forced laughter ]

13:39.886 --> 13:41.886
[ French techno music playing ]
<i> ♪ L'amour ♪</i>

13:41.888 --> 13:43.488
<i> ♪ Le coeur ♪</i>

13:43.490 --> 13:45.758
<i> ♪ Se jous ♪</i>

13:45.760 --> 13:47.359
<i> ♪ Bonjour ♪</i>

13:47.361 --> 13:49.294
<i> ♪ Monsieur ♪</i>

13:49.296 --> 13:51.397
<i> ♪ Glamour ♪</i>

13:53.033 --> 13:55.100
<i> ♪ Bonheur ♪</i>

13:55.102 --> 13:57.101
<i> ♪ Danseur ♪</i>

13:57.103 --> 14:00.505
<i> ♪ Voyeur ♪</i>

14:00.507 --> 14:02.975
<i> ♪ Meilleur ♪</i>

14:02.977 --> 14:06.378
♪♪

14:06.380 --> 14:07.912
Isn't this
hilarious?

14:07.914 --> 14:11.984
It will be -- when you dump
clam chowder on his head.

14:11.986 --> 14:14.520
[ Music continues ]

14:17.458 --> 14:19.658
[ Scattered applause ]

14:19.660 --> 14:22.861
Pull the rope.
It'll be hilarious.

14:22.863 --> 14:24.529
Um...

14:24.531 --> 14:28.400
[ Scattered applause ]

14:28.402 --> 14:30.402
Why is she not
doing what you say?

14:30.404 --> 14:33.137
I guess
she doesn't want this.

14:33.139 --> 14:35.674
I'd get to be
a Golden Girl?

14:35.676 --> 14:38.477
[ Splash ]

14:38.479 --> 14:39.944
[ Laughter ]

14:39.946 --> 14:41.714
Cream-covered boy?

14:42.949 --> 14:44.016
Cream-covered boy.

14:44.018 --> 14:46.885
Wait a minute.
This has to be a trap.

14:46.887 --> 14:50.389
But, then again,
it's better to know.

14:52.426 --> 14:53.825
[ School bell rings ]

14:53.827 --> 14:55.627
You look great,
Francine.

14:55.629 --> 14:58.496
You look like you got hit
by a bag of dicks, Dorothy.

14:58.498 --> 15:00.366
[ Laughter ]

15:00.368 --> 15:02.735
Oh, hi, Francine.

15:05.305 --> 15:06.704
Aw, man!

15:06.706 --> 15:08.706
They put my name
backwards.

15:08.708 --> 15:11.042
Steve
killed himself!
What?!

15:11.044 --> 15:12.644
Is the type of thing
you might hear,

15:12.646 --> 15:14.646
considering what you did
to him yesterday.

15:14.648 --> 15:15.847
What were
you thinking?

15:15.849 --> 15:18.650
Oh, my God, Roger,
I'm a monster!

15:18.652 --> 15:19.985
What am I gonna do?

15:19.987 --> 15:22.388
I don't effing know!
This is a disaster.

15:22.390 --> 15:26.191
[ Grunting ]

15:26.193 --> 15:27.593
[ Groaning ]

15:27.595 --> 15:29.861
I think I have
to apologize to Steve.

15:29.863 --> 15:32.264
Oh.
Yeah, that'll work.

15:32.266 --> 15:34.800
[ Birds chirping ]

15:37.070 --> 15:38.337
Hey, Steve?

15:40.340 --> 15:41.740
Are you okay, hon?

15:41.742 --> 15:43.609
Oh, hey, Mom.
Yeah, I'm good.

15:43.611 --> 15:45.944
I was just smelling
my pillow super hard.

15:45.946 --> 15:48.213
Have you ever wondered
what dreams smell like?

15:48.215 --> 15:49.547
[ Inhales deeply ]

15:49.549 --> 15:51.550
I think
they smell like this.

15:52.886 --> 15:54.886
What's up?

15:54.888 --> 15:57.889
I...wanted to talk to you
about what happened

15:57.891 --> 16:00.092
at the French Club
Fashion Show.

16:00.094 --> 16:01.627
Oh, what a disaster.

16:01.629 --> 16:03.695
Barry ate the baguette
instead of walking with it,

16:03.697 --> 16:05.631
and, of course, all my friends
are just ugly,

16:05.633 --> 16:08.233
so that hurt the fashion
in the end, unfortunately.

16:08.235 --> 16:10.502
No, Steve,
the chowder.

16:10.504 --> 16:12.037
That was me.

16:12.039 --> 16:15.240
I'm so, so sorry.

16:15.242 --> 16:16.442
Oh, I knew that.

16:16.444 --> 16:17.976
You're not mad?

16:17.978 --> 16:20.446
Nah. I wasn't even covered
in chowder for that long.

16:20.448 --> 16:24.316
Roger and who I assume
are the other janitors
licked it clean off me.

16:24.318 --> 16:28.186
Small price to pay for getting
to express what's in my soul.

16:28.188 --> 16:29.787
Wow.

16:29.789 --> 16:32.790
You really don't care
what people think.

16:32.792 --> 16:33.859
Can you teach me?

16:33.861 --> 16:35.794
I can teach you
what Sheila taught me.

16:35.796 --> 16:38.063
She had a pretty good reputation
as a guidance counselor

16:38.065 --> 16:39.998
until she sent
pictures of her butthole

16:40.000 --> 16:41.266
to that sophomore.

16:41.268 --> 16:42.534
Hmm.

16:42.536 --> 16:46.204
Maybe you could
do that for me.

16:46.206 --> 16:48.674
The guidance part.

16:48.676 --> 16:51.410
[ Sobbing ]

16:53.747 --> 16:55.147
[ Knock on door ]

16:55.149 --> 16:58.150
Go away!

16:58.152 --> 17:01.353
Don't shut me out,
Jeff!

17:01.355 --> 17:04.089
I'm so sorry
you lost your hat.

17:04.091 --> 17:09.827
But we'll get through this --
together!

17:09.829 --> 17:11.629
I love you, babe.

17:11.631 --> 17:14.400
[ Both sobbing ]

17:17.437 --> 17:19.171
[ School bell rings ]

17:19.173 --> 17:22.708
Okay, Francine, let's talk about
why you're such a Debbie.

17:22.710 --> 17:24.042
I'm not a Debbie!

17:24.044 --> 17:26.311
It's important
to be honest in here.

17:26.313 --> 17:28.313
Okay,
maybe I'm a Debbie.

17:28.315 --> 17:31.917
But when I was in high school,
they called it being a Herb.

17:31.919 --> 17:34.652
Who called you a Herb --
bitches?

17:34.654 --> 17:37.189
Yes!
The archery team.

17:37.191 --> 17:39.124
I never expressed myself

17:39.126 --> 17:42.460
because I was always afraid
they might think I was lame.

17:42.462 --> 17:43.661
I see.

17:43.663 --> 17:44.662
Well, what would
you have done

17:44.664 --> 17:46.464
if there were no
archery team?

17:46.466 --> 17:48.200
Break dance.
[ Laughs ]

17:48.202 --> 17:49.735
Oh, you're serious.
Hmm.

17:49.737 --> 17:52.003
Oh, my God!
You're judging me.

17:52.005 --> 17:55.073
And that shouldn't matter
because...?

17:55.075 --> 17:58.544
Because break dancing
is in my soul.

17:58.546 --> 18:00.078
That's right!

18:00.080 --> 18:02.881
Hmm, I'm pretty good
at this therapy thing.

18:02.883 --> 18:05.217
Hey, Mertz,
tell me your problem.

18:05.219 --> 18:08.019
My foster father
adopted me for the money,

18:08.021 --> 18:10.355
and now he beats me
with a wrench.

18:10.357 --> 18:12.891
Out of my depth
immediately!

18:12.893 --> 18:14.893
[ Indistinct conversations ]

18:14.895 --> 18:16.662
[ Light switch flicking ]

18:17.497 --> 18:19.497
♪ If I wanna take a guy ♪

18:19.499 --> 18:20.698
♪ Home with me tonight ♪

18:20.700 --> 18:22.434
♪ It's none of your business ♪

18:22.436 --> 18:25.503
♪ And if she wanna be a freak
and sell it on the weekend ♪

18:25.505 --> 18:26.972
♪ It's none of your business ♪

18:26.974 --> 18:28.974
♪ Now you
shouldn't even get into ♪

18:28.976 --> 18:30.376
♪ Who I'm givin' skins to ♪

18:30.378 --> 18:31.910
♪ It's none of your business ♪

18:31.912 --> 18:33.779
♪ So don't
try to change my mind ♪

18:33.781 --> 18:35.180
♪ I'll tell you one more time ♪

18:35.182 --> 18:36.848
♪ It's none of your business ♪

18:36.850 --> 18:37.583
♪ Now -- ♪

18:37.585 --> 18:38.716
[ Grunts ]

18:38.718 --> 18:41.920
[ Laughter ]

18:41.922 --> 18:43.922
Are -- Are you
all right?

18:43.924 --> 18:46.524
Did -- Did they love it?

18:46.526 --> 18:47.793
It was terrible.

18:47.795 --> 18:50.095
But that's not
the important part.

18:52.800 --> 18:55.401
Thank you.
You're right.

18:55.403 --> 18:57.069
You guys,
I'm starting to think

18:57.071 --> 18:59.271
that she's friends
with that dweeb.

18:59.273 --> 19:03.275
Well, for your information,
this isn't my dweeb friend.

19:03.277 --> 19:05.010
He's my dweeb son.

19:05.012 --> 19:08.480
And he doesn't care
what other people think.

19:08.482 --> 19:10.148
But<i> I</i> do.

19:10.150 --> 19:11.817
Uh-oh.

19:11.819 --> 19:14.886
And next time
you mess with a Debbie,

19:14.888 --> 19:17.289
make sure it's not
a grown-ass Debbie

19:17.291 --> 19:21.159
with access to your confidential
psychological assessments.

19:21.161 --> 19:22.894
Mom, you don't have
to do this.

19:22.896 --> 19:26.098
You can walk away knowing you
showed everyone your true self.

19:26.100 --> 19:29.101
Yeah, but I didn't show
my true self.

19:29.103 --> 19:30.502
I'm not a dancer.

19:30.504 --> 19:32.570
I'm a bad bitch

19:32.572 --> 19:34.973
who lays waste
to her enemies.

19:34.975 --> 19:38.510
Blanche, you transferred
from your last school

19:38.512 --> 19:41.913
because the kids found out
that you carried around

19:41.915 --> 19:45.050
a piece of your own shit
in your backpack!

19:45.052 --> 19:46.251
All: Ew!

19:46.253 --> 19:49.655
Sophia, you were taken away
from your parents

19:49.657 --> 19:52.124
because they are
brother and sister.

19:52.126 --> 19:53.325
[ All gasp ]

19:53.327 --> 19:54.860
And Dorothy...

19:54.862 --> 19:56.128
Let me guess --
You figured out

19:56.130 --> 19:58.396
Austin's death
wasn't an accident.

19:58.398 --> 19:59.998
No.

20:00.000 --> 20:02.468
Your file just says
you grind your teeth.

20:02.470 --> 20:03.869
Did you murder someone?

20:03.871 --> 20:05.603
She grinds her teeth!

20:05.605 --> 20:08.540
The Golden Girls
are a bunch of losers!

20:08.542 --> 20:10.942
Their reign of terror
is over!

20:10.944 --> 20:14.546
The age of Mertz
begins now!

20:14.548 --> 20:16.414
[ Cheering ]

20:16.416 --> 20:17.549
Stan: Francine!

20:17.551 --> 20:18.816
Francine!

20:18.818 --> 20:20.218
Will you go to the prom
with me?

20:20.220 --> 20:22.420
Stan,
we're already married.

20:22.422 --> 20:24.490
That's not a yes,
but that's not a no.

20:24.492 --> 20:25.557
Now start laughing.

20:25.559 --> 20:27.359
[ Forced laughter ]

20:27.361 --> 20:30.229
Are you sure
this is a thing that works?

20:31.832 --> 20:33.699
I'm scared.

20:33.701 --> 20:34.900
I understand.

20:34.902 --> 20:38.037
But our new life
begins today.

20:40.174 --> 20:42.240
Welcome to Lids.
I'm Parker.

20:42.242 --> 20:43.976
What can I help
you find today?

20:58.325 --> 21:00.159
Bye! Have a beautiful time!
